'''TM-28''' was a [[Soyuz programme | Soyuz]] mission to the [[Mir]] space station.

==Crew==
Launched:
*1 [[Gennady Padalka]] (1) - Commander - {{RUS}}
*2 [[Sergei Avdeyev]] (3) - Flight Engineer - {{RUS}}
*3 [[Yuri Baturin]] (1) - Research Cosmonaut - {{RUS}}

Landed:
*1 [[Gennady Padalka]] (1) - Commander - {{RUS}}
*2 [[Ivan Bella]] (1) - Flight Engineer - {{SVK}}

==Mission Accomplishments==
*Docked with [[Mir]]
*Baturin is first [[Russia]]n [[politician]] in space
*Padalka and Avdeyev performed an [[extra-vehicular activity|EVA]] on 15.09.1998 (30 m) into the module [[Spektr]] (new cables connected for solar structures).

==Notes==
*Padalka and Avdeyev became 26th resident crew of Mir.
*Baturin landed on [[August 25]], [[1998]] (5:22 UT) with [[Soyuz TM-27]].
*Avdeyev landed on [[August 28]], [[1999]] (0:41 UT) with [[Soyuz TM-29]].

